**Note:** By default, the main window has a minimum size of `Vector2i(64, 64)`. This prevents issues that can arise when the window is resized to a near-zero size.
**Note:** Using third-party tools, it is possible for users to disable window geometry restrictions and therefore bypass this limit.Returns the size of the window specified by `window_id` (in pixels), including the borders drawn by the operating system. See also `window_get_size()`.Returns the mode of the given window.Sets window mode for the given window to `mode`.
**Note:** On Android, setting it to `WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN` or `WINDOW_MODE_EXCLUSIVE_FULLSCREEN` will enable immersive mode.
