**Note:** This method is implemented on Windows and macOS.Sets the window icon (usually displayed in the top-left corner) in the operating system's *native* format. The file at `filename` must be in `.ico` format on Windows or `.icns` on macOS. By using specially crafted `.ico` or `.icns` icons, `set_native_icon()` allows specifying different icons depending on the size the icon is displayed at. This size is determined by the operating system and user preferences (including the display scale factor). To use icons in other formats, use `set_icon()` instead.
