This can be used to prevent Godot from skipping rendering when no normal windows are visible.Unregisters an `Object` representing an additional output, that was registered via `register_additional_output()`.Returns `true` if any additional outputs have been registered via `register_additional_output()`.The ID that refers to a screen that does not exist. This is returned by some `DisplayServer` methods if no screen matches the requested result.Represents the screen containing the mouse pointer.
