**Note:** The equivalent node is `LightmapGI`.Set the textures on the given `lightmap` GI instance to the texture array pointed to by the `light` RID. If the lightmap texture was baked with `LightmapGI.directional` set to `true`, then `uses_sh` must also be `true`.Used to inform the renderer what exposure normalization value was used while baking the lightmap. This value will be used and modulated at run time to ensure that the lightmap maintains a consistent level of exposure even if the scene-wide exposure normalization is changed at run time. For more information see `camera_attributes_set_exposure()`.Creates a GPU-based particle system and adds it to the RenderingServer. It can be accessed with the RID that is returned. This RID will be used in all `particles_*` RenderingServer functions.
