than zero, it is used as font oversampling factor, otherwise viewport oversampling settings are used.Draw outline of the single line of text into a canvas item at a given position, with `color`. `pos` specifies the top left corner of the bounding box. If `oversampling` is greater than zero, it is used as font oversampling factor, otherwise viewport oversampling settings are used.Draw drop cap into a canvas item at a given position, with `color`. `pos` specifies the top left corner of the bounding box. If `oversampling` is greater than zero, it is used as font oversampling factor, otherwise viewport oversampling settings are used.Draw drop cap outline into a canvas item at a given position, with `color`. `pos` specifies the top left corner of the bounding box. If `oversampling` is greater than zero, it is used as font oversampling factor, otherwise viewport oversampling settings are used.Returns caret character offset at the specified coordinates. This function always returns a valid position.Custom punctuation character list, used for word breaking. If set to empty string, server defaults are used.Paragraph horizontal alignment.Line breaking rules. For more info see `TextServer`.The clipping behavior when the text exceeds the paragraph's set width.Paragraph width.Limits the lines of text shown.A server interface for font management and text rendering.

`TextServer` is the API backend for managing fonts and rendering text.
**Note:** This is a low-level API, consider using `TextLine`, `TextParagraph`, and `Font` classes instead.
This is an abstract class, so to get the currently active `TextServer` instance, use the following code:


```gdscript
var ts = TextServerManager.get_primary_interface()
```


Returns `true` if the server supports a feature.Returns the name of the server interface.Returns text server features, see `Feature`.Loads optional TextServer database (e.g. ICU break iterators and dictionaries).
